WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:02.369 --> 00:00:02.785
<i>SCOFIELD: Previously
on</i> Prison Break.

2
00:00:02.870 --> 00:00:03.947
Mr. Kim.

3
00:00:03.971 --> 00:00:05.370
Sara Tancredi. I'm on it.

4
00:00:05.439 --> 00:00:07.768
Is pursuing her the best
use of your time? It is.

5
00:00:07.792 --> 00:00:08.918
I'll let the President know.

6
00:00:08.942 --> 00:00:10.792
I contact the
President directly.

7
00:00:10.861 --> 00:00:12.093
I'll contact her.

8
00:00:16.934 --> 00:00:18.951
<i>IVES: No family with
Patoshik? Nothing?</i>

9
00:00:19.019 --> 00:00:22.339
<i>FBI AGENT: Yeah. Till about four
years ago when he killed them all.</i>

10
00:00:23.273 --> 00:00:24.623
<i>MAHONE: Fernando Sucre.</i>

11
00:00:24.691 --> 00:00:26.286
<i>He was in Las Vegas around 2:00.</i>

12
00:00:26.310 --> 00:00:28.827
Out west. just like
Bagwell and Franklin.

13
00:00:28.896 --> 00:00:30.278
You know D.B. Cooper?

14
00:00:30.364 --> 00:00:33.648
The money's in Utah. and
they're all going to get it.

15
00:00:33.717 --> 00:00:35.818
You're one of them
Fox River boys.

16
00:00:42.276 --> 00:00:43.276
(GROANS)

17
00:00:44.778 --> 00:00:45.805
Come on. You got the map?

18
00:00:45.829 --> 00:00:47.929
No. Someone else does.

19
00:00:47.998 --> 00:00:49.581
Before I destroyed it.

20
00:00:49.650 --> 00:00:51.766
I committed it to my
photographic memory.

21
00:00:51.835 --> 00:00:55.153
I have the information. you
have the manual requirements

22
00:00:55.222 --> 00:00:58.340
necessary to unearth
Westmoreland's buried booty.

23
00:00:58.409 --> 00:01:00.369
Get in. Okay.

24
00:01:02.363 --> 00:01:04.145
T-BAG: Should be dead ahead.

25
00:01:06.016 --> 00:01:08.300
T-BAG: The
bastards built over it.

26
00:01:08.369 --> 00:01:09.951
It's gone.

27
00:01:11.000 --> 00:01:17.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

28
00:01:49.660 --> 00:01:50.926
(GRUNTS)

29
00:02:23.043 --> 00:02:24.821
We have to open
up in 15 minutes.

30
00:02:24.845 --> 00:02:26.238
So? It doesn't
matter. I dare you.

31
00:02:26.262 --> 00:02:27.596
I said... I said. no.

32
00:02:27.664 --> 00:02:29.264
I dare you. Please?

33
00:02:37.424 --> 00:02:38.940
(SCREAMS)

34
00:03:04.218 --> 00:03:06.658
LINCOLN: The ranch
is gone. Michael.

35
00:03:07.804 --> 00:03:09.871
Well. the 5 million
might not be.

36
00:03:09.940 --> 00:03:12.123
T-BAG: And you
gonna find it how?

37
00:03:12.192 --> 00:03:14.643
What. you got a divining
rod tattooed on your ass?

38
00:03:14.711 --> 00:03:16.456
I don't wanna hear
anything out of your mouth

39
00:03:16.480 --> 00:03:20.882
other than what your photographic
memory spits out regarding that map!

40
00:03:20.950 --> 00:03:22.929
You watch your
tone with me. boy.

41
00:03:22.953 --> 00:03:25.215
I will watch you get tossed
to the side of the road

42
00:03:25.239 --> 00:03:27.372
to fend for yourself. boy.

43
00:03:27.440 --> 00:03:30.074
Because if you can't
remember where that silo was.

44
00:03:30.143 --> 00:03:32.160
you're worthless to us.

45
00:03:32.229 --> 00:03:33.506
TWEENER: Yo. fools. let me out!

46
00:03:33.530 --> 00:03:34.746
Shut up.

47
00:03:34.814 --> 00:03:36.364
The map!

48
00:03:36.450 --> 00:03:38.294
Okay. okay. okay. all
right. all right. all right.

49
00:03:38.318 --> 00:03:40.279
TWEENER: Let me
out. boss. The ranch.

50
00:03:40.303 --> 00:03:42.214
The ranch was in
the center of a box.

51
00:03:42.238 --> 00:03:45.757
Sheep Road on one side.
Kokosing Road perpendicular.

52
00:03:45.825 --> 00:03:49.694
In the center of the property
was the ranch house.

53
00:03:49.763 --> 00:03:52.024
And the ranch house
was surrounded by trees.

54
00:03:52.048 --> 00:03:55.200
TWEENER: I can't breathe
in here. man. Let me out.

55
00:03:55.269 --> 00:03:56.517
(SCOFIELD SIGHS)

56
00:04:05.111 --> 00:04:07.729
Every tree here is
a year old. at most.

57
00:04:08.799 --> 00:04:10.565
Except those.

58
00:04:12.786 --> 00:04:14.485
Where is the silo?

59
00:04:17.574 --> 00:04:20.024
Inside the trees.

60
00:04:20.094 --> 00:04:22.927
I wanna say on the left.

61
00:04:22.996 --> 00:04:25.980
but that may have been a barn.

62
00:04:26.049 --> 00:04:27.749
I remembered the
best I could. gents.

63
00:04:27.818 --> 00:04:31.253
but I didn't know this place would
now be smothered in tract homes.

64
00:04:31.321 --> 00:04:34.556
so. you know. I'm sorry that
I'm not Rain Man over here.

65
00:04:39.179 --> 00:04:40.273
Alex Mahone. How are you?

66
00:04:40.297 --> 00:04:41.529
Lyle Sands.

67
00:04:41.598 --> 00:04:43.798
We've been briefed
on all the men at large.

68
00:04:43.867 --> 00:04:46.896
The full force and resources of
the entire Salt Lake City field office

69
00:04:46.920 --> 00:04:48.353
are at your disposal.

70
00:04:48.421 --> 00:04:50.366
Thank you. Do you have
those files my office requested

71
00:04:50.390 --> 00:04:51.406
on the D.B. Cooper case?

72
00:04:51.475 --> 00:04:52.841
We're pulling them now.

73
00:04:52.909 --> 00:04:55.177
And this is the D.B. Cooper
case from 30 years ago?

74
00:04:55.245 --> 00:04:57.957
Correct. If I can get those files
immediately. I'd appreciate it.

75
00:04:57.981 --> 00:05:00.181
Hey. sorry. but I have to ask.

76
00:05:00.250 --> 00:05:02.711
Aren't you here for the
Fox River Eight? I am.

77
00:05:02.735 --> 00:05:06.805
And they're here in Utah
to get D.B. Cooper's money.

78
00:05:06.874 --> 00:05:08.173
So how about those files. Lyle?

79
00:05:09.325 --> 00:05:11.159
T-BAG: Silo.

80
00:05:11.227 --> 00:05:13.144
Silo. silo. silo. silo.

81
00:05:13.213 --> 00:05:14.863
This is stupid.

82
00:05:14.932 --> 00:05:16.342
We're gonna get made out here.

83
00:05:16.366 --> 00:05:18.083
Shut it. I think I remember.

84
00:05:19.336 --> 00:05:21.203
If I had to bet. I'd lay it all

85
00:05:21.271 --> 00:05:24.639
on the silo being on the left of
the ranch house inside the trees.

86
00:05:24.708 --> 00:05:27.275
No. It's outside the trees.

87
00:05:28.195 --> 00:05:30.178
Right there.

88
00:05:30.247 --> 00:05:32.314
You see those two trees?

89
00:05:32.382 --> 00:05:34.432
They're shorter than the rest.

90
00:05:34.501 --> 00:05:36.668
They were all planted
at the same time.

91
00:05:36.737 --> 00:05:38.870
but those two didn't
get as much sunlight.

92
00:05:38.938 --> 00:05:41.139
Something was in their way.

93
00:05:41.208 --> 00:05:43.024
SCOFIELD: The silo.

94
00:05:43.093 --> 00:05:45.961
Our money should be right
there under that garage.

95
00:05:46.029 --> 00:05:48.113
You better be right. boy.

96
00:05:48.165 --> 00:05:50.415
SCOFIELD: This isn't
a high-end subdivision.

97
00:05:50.484 --> 00:05:52.183
They slapped this
place up overnight.

98
00:05:52.252 --> 00:05:54.686
The silo's foundations
might still be there.

99
00:05:54.755 --> 00:05:56.938
To save money. they
probably just laid the concrete

100
00:05:57.007 --> 00:05:59.124
for the garage floor
right on top of it.

101
00:05:59.192 --> 00:06:00.192
We'll dig straight down.

102
00:06:00.260 --> 00:06:01.604
If we hit the
foundation. we stay.

103
00:06:01.628 --> 00:06:04.162
If not. we go.

104
00:06:04.231 --> 00:06:05.696
Let's do it.

105
00:06:05.765 --> 00:06:07.499
TWEENER: Let me out of here.

106
00:06:09.736 --> 00:06:11.019
Oh. man.

107
00:06:12.272 --> 00:06:13.272
Mmm-mmm.

108
00:06:19.246 --> 00:06:22.396
Ain't no problem that a
screwdriver to her temple won't fix.

109
00:07:03.990 --> 00:07:05.807
People die all the time. boys.

110
00:07:05.876 --> 00:07:08.944
$5 million comes
once in a lifetime.

111
00:07:09.012 --> 00:07:11.162
TWEENER: Let me out of
here. man. Come on. boss.

112
00:07:11.230 --> 00:07:15.016
We gotta do something. and it's
not gonna involve hurting anyone.

113
00:07:21.141 --> 00:07:22.474
I got an idea.

114
00:07:22.543 --> 00:07:24.876
First. we're gonna
need some supplies.

115
00:07:42.162 --> 00:07:45.446
110%. I do not agree with this.

116
00:07:45.515 --> 00:07:48.032
Everybody's got to pitch
in to make this happen.

117
00:07:48.101 --> 00:07:51.919
But back in the big house. the
boy proved he couldn't be trusted.

118
00:07:51.988 --> 00:07:53.683
Which is why
we're doing it here.

119
00:07:53.707 --> 00:07:57.058
If he gets caught in town. he
ain't got a clue where the house is.

120
00:07:57.127 --> 00:08:00.344
Besides. you're the one
we can't turn our backs on.

121
00:08:03.833 --> 00:08:04.873
(GROANS)

122
00:08:07.036 --> 00:08:09.204
Oh. I could have
died in there. man.

123
00:08:11.725 --> 00:08:14.175
Well. guess what? I
need you to do something.

124
00:08:14.244 --> 00:08:16.795
I need you to do
something for me.

125
00:08:16.864 --> 00:08:18.212
I want my cut of the money.

126
00:08:18.281 --> 00:08:22.067
Well. we'll talk once you
prove we can trust you.

127
00:08:22.135 --> 00:08:23.401
What do I got to do?

128
00:08:23.469 --> 00:08:25.014
I want you to go back
to that garden center

129
00:08:25.038 --> 00:08:27.188
and get everything on this list.

130
00:08:27.857 --> 00:08:29.424
And gas up the car.

131
00:08:32.061 --> 00:08:34.712
We'll meet you right
back here in an hour.

132
00:08:36.650 --> 00:08:38.767
All right. And. David.

133
00:08:42.005 --> 00:08:44.055
don't screw this up.

134
00:08:44.123 --> 00:08:46.323
This ain't Fox
River no more. man.

135
00:08:47.694 --> 00:08:49.877
Looking at the real deal now.

136
00:08:50.997 --> 00:08:52.546
But I want my cut.

137
00:08:55.985 --> 00:08:57.702
Back in an hour.

138
00:09:03.210 --> 00:09:04.459
Let's go.

139
00:09:06.847 --> 00:09:08.079
Mistake.

140
00:09:08.815 --> 00:09:10.465
Big mistake.

141
00:09:25.648 --> 00:09:27.198
(MOTORCYCLE APPROACHING)

142
00:09:40.314 --> 00:09:41.846
Oh. come on. man.

143
00:10:07.341 --> 00:10:08.539
(CHUCKLES)

144
00:10:09.476 --> 00:10:11.409
Am I glad to see you.

145
00:10:12.729 --> 00:10:14.212
Did you walk here?

146
00:10:14.281 --> 00:10:18.616
(STAMMERING) No.
It's just a long story. man.

147
00:10:18.685 --> 00:10:20.746
Thought you were
meeting up with your family.

148
00:10:20.770 --> 00:10:23.137
I met a few roadblocks.

149
00:10:23.206 --> 00:10:24.288
And you?

150
00:10:24.357 --> 00:10:25.373
Yeah.

151
00:10:26.642 --> 00:10:29.293
Let me guess. you're
going to Tooele.

152
00:10:29.362 --> 00:10:31.712
Yeah.

153
00:10:31.781 --> 00:10:35.383
Well. looks like we're
going the same direction.

154
00:10:35.452 --> 00:10:37.968
Hopefully we're not too late.

155
00:10:38.037 --> 00:10:39.754
Can I hitch a ride?

156
00:10:41.624 --> 00:10:42.957
Hey. look.

157
00:10:47.447 --> 00:10:49.347
I'll make it worth your while.

158
00:10:51.785 --> 00:10:53.518
WHEELER: Got
some good news. sir.

159
00:10:53.587 --> 00:10:55.720
Got our first tip on Patoshik.

160
00:10:55.789 --> 00:10:59.523
Spotted at a burger joint
in Cedar Grove. Wisconsin.

161
00:10:59.592 --> 00:11:01.320
Just hand it over to
local authorities for now.

162
00:11:01.344 --> 00:11:04.212
The only thing we're working
today is Utah and D.B. Cooper.

163
00:11:04.281 --> 00:11:05.546
Got it.

164
00:11:07.150 --> 00:11:09.584
Lyle.

165
00:11:09.653 --> 00:11:11.964
There's a guy here listed as
having the only D.B. Cooper bill

166
00:11:11.988 --> 00:11:14.028
ever found in circulation.
Harold Jenkins.

167
00:11:14.090 --> 00:11:16.491
Yeah. D.B. bought gas
from Jenkins with a hundred

168
00:11:16.559 --> 00:11:18.509
on the day of the hijacking.

169
00:11:18.578 --> 00:11:21.312
We checked the serial
numbers and they matched.

170
00:11:21.381 --> 00:11:22.880
You worked the case?

171
00:11:23.750 --> 00:11:25.133
Fresh out of the academy.

172
00:11:25.202 --> 00:11:27.485
And nobody's cracked it yet.

173
00:11:27.554 --> 00:11:30.600
What makes you think that these
escapees know where the money is?

174
00:11:30.624 --> 00:11:33.152
Because they may have been
locked up with the real D.B. Cooper.

175
00:11:33.176 --> 00:11:35.476
This Jenkins from the
gas station. he still alive?

176
00:11:35.544 --> 00:11:38.095
Should be. He was
only 18 at the time.

177
00:11:38.164 --> 00:11:39.747
Well. let's go say hi to him.

178
00:12:14.250 --> 00:12:15.490
<i>AUTOMATED VOICE: We're sorry.</i>

179
00:12:15.518 --> 00:12:17.352
<i>Your call cannot be
completed as dialed.</i>

180
00:12:17.420 --> 00:12:19.771
<i>Please check the
number and dial again.</i>

181
00:12:35.422 --> 00:12:37.433
<i>KIM: Do you have
updates on Sara Tancredi?</i>

182
00:12:37.457 --> 00:12:38.901
I assume that's why you're here.

183
00:12:38.925 --> 00:12:43.361
Yes. Scofield sent her a
message through the mail.

184
00:12:43.429 --> 00:12:45.997
a phone number that
was disconnected.

185
00:12:48.534 --> 00:12:51.035
You know. to be honest.

186
00:12:51.104 --> 00:12:53.504
I was expecting to
brief the President.

187
00:12:55.675 --> 00:12:58.325
Yeah. about that.

188
00:12:58.394 --> 00:13:02.680
right now. as you can
imagine. Caroline's quite busy.

189
00:13:02.749 --> 00:13:04.181
She's always been busy.

190
00:13:04.250 --> 00:13:05.811
I've been working side by
side with her for 15 years.

191
00:13:05.835 --> 00:13:09.203
Paul. she's the President
of the United States now.

192
00:13:09.272 --> 00:13:11.989
Yes. Bill. and I
helped to put her there.

193
00:13:12.058 --> 00:13:15.226
Well. if you'd like for
her to remain in office.

194
00:13:15.294 --> 00:13:18.646
you'll take my advice and just
stay on the sidelines for now.

195
00:13:20.050 --> 00:13:21.611
She needs to be
completely insulated

196
00:13:21.635 --> 00:13:23.668
from anything regarding
Lincoln Burrows.

197
00:13:27.206 --> 00:13:28.789
I want to talk to her.

198
00:13:31.527 --> 00:13:33.227
You report to me now

199
00:13:33.296 --> 00:13:34.912
and only me.

200
00:13:34.981 --> 00:13:37.126
You're not to try and contact
Caroline again without my approval.

201
00:13:37.150 --> 00:13:40.584
and you don't show
up here unannounced.

202
00:13:43.206 --> 00:13:47.391
Finish the job you
were given. get Burrows.

203
00:13:47.460 --> 00:13:49.939
If you're telling me the road to
him leads through Sara Tancredi.

204
00:13:49.963 --> 00:13:53.030
by all means. pursue it.

205
00:13:53.099 --> 00:13:54.360
And once that's
been accomplished

206
00:13:54.384 --> 00:13:56.984
and this whole thing goes away.

207
00:13:57.052 --> 00:14:00.321
we'll go about transitioning
you back into Caroline's life.

208
00:14:03.677 --> 00:14:05.877
Now do you have
anything else on Sara?

209
00:14:05.912 --> 00:14:08.596
The President has
unwavering faith in you.

210
00:14:08.665 --> 00:14:10.960
Wants to make sure you go
through the Senate approval process

211
00:14:10.984 --> 00:14:12.166
with your eyes wide open.

212
00:14:12.235 --> 00:14:13.412
So what are we up against?

213
00:14:13.436 --> 00:14:15.080
Key allies in the
House and Senate

214
00:14:15.104 --> 00:14:17.605
are Meyerhoff. Barnwell
and Summerville.

215
00:14:17.673 --> 00:14:19.184
We're counting on
them to sway the middle.

216
00:14:19.208 --> 00:14:21.074
Who's the opposition?

217
00:14:21.143 --> 00:14:24.745
Senators Blake and Killoren have openly
vocalized their opposition to you as VP.

218
00:14:24.814 --> 00:14:27.181
Any indication as to why?

219
00:14:27.250 --> 00:14:28.961
Political payback for
the President's vote

220
00:14:28.985 --> 00:14:30.930
on the energy bill last month.

221
00:14:30.954 --> 00:14:34.154
Took them by surprise
and they don't like surprises.

222
00:14:38.044 --> 00:14:40.978
Dad. Lance. this
is my father. Frank.

223
00:14:41.047 --> 00:14:42.797
Pleasure to meet you. sir.

224
00:14:42.883 --> 00:14:44.276
It's nothing to lose sleep over.

225
00:14:44.300 --> 00:14:47.151
Frankly. the biggest
issue we have to address

226
00:14:47.220 --> 00:14:49.870
are the charges
facing your daughter.

227
00:14:49.939 --> 00:14:51.639
Governor. are you with me?

228
00:14:52.975 --> 00:14:54.375
Absolutely.

229
00:15:03.469 --> 00:15:04.902
(MUFFLED YELLS)

230
00:15:09.125 --> 00:15:10.841
No. just chill. dawg.

231
00:15:10.910 --> 00:15:14.696
Listen. once we roll out.
we bounce out of town.

232
00:15:14.764 --> 00:15:16.948
we'll drop a dime
and they will find you.

233
00:15:17.016 --> 00:15:19.350
Just be quiet. Just chill. man.

234
00:15:20.470 --> 00:15:22.419
(MUFFLED SCREAMS)

235
00:15:25.041 --> 00:15:26.991
(POUNDING ON DOOR)

236
00:15:34.000 --> 00:15:35.000
(DOOR OPENING)

237
00:15:35.985 --> 00:15:37.167
Woody?

238
00:15:39.606 --> 00:15:42.256
Where are you at? Woody?

239
00:15:53.670 --> 00:15:55.219
(CELL PHONE DIALING)

240
00:15:58.992 --> 00:16:00.858
CHET: I need Sheriff Williams.

241
00:16:01.894 --> 00:16:03.410
Yeah. I'll hold.

242
00:16:04.113 --> 00:16:05.713
(MUFFLED YELLS CONTINUE)

243
00:16:10.553 --> 00:16:12.053
Woody?

244
00:16:28.805 --> 00:16:30.515
Where did you learn
about electricity?

245
00:16:30.539 --> 00:16:33.608
I used to steal copper
wiring from transformer boxes.

246
00:16:33.676 --> 00:16:36.560
and then sell them on the
docks. make a few bucks.

247
00:16:36.613 --> 00:16:38.796
When you were at
school. of course.

248
00:16:49.359 --> 00:16:51.559
I was just looking. pretty.

249
00:16:51.628 --> 00:16:53.193
What's that old chestnut?

250
00:16:53.263 --> 00:16:55.407
"I can look at the menu.
Doesn't mean I'm gonna eat."

251
00:16:55.431 --> 00:16:58.199
We get in. we get
the money. we get out.

252
00:16:58.267 --> 00:17:00.267
That's it. No. Absolutely.

253
00:17:11.463 --> 00:17:12.746
We're good.

254
00:17:15.869 --> 00:17:17.685
Now it's just up to the kid.

255
00:17:23.543 --> 00:17:24.675
Did you get everything?

256
00:17:24.744 --> 00:17:26.093
Yeah. Yeah. I got it.

257
00:17:27.062 --> 00:17:28.195
(EXHALES DEEPLY)

258
00:17:30.617 --> 00:17:32.483
(TWEENER BREATHING HEAVILY)

259
00:17:32.552 --> 00:17:34.402
(KEY RATTLING IN LOCK)

260
00:17:47.249 --> 00:17:48.327
What?

261
00:17:48.351 --> 00:17:49.833
Nothing. it's cool. I...

262
00:17:50.987 --> 00:17:52.537
What? Whoa.

263
00:17:53.456 --> 00:17:56.056
Okay. Check it.

264
00:17:56.125 --> 00:17:57.575
This fool came in the shop.

265
00:17:57.644 --> 00:17:59.409
He was acting all shady.

266
00:17:59.478 --> 00:18:01.006
He got a bad vibe. so he
picked up his celly phone.

267
00:18:01.030 --> 00:18:03.464
he started to make a
call. so I popped him.

268
00:18:03.532 --> 00:18:04.609
You did what?

269
00:18:04.633 --> 00:18:05.966
I hit him with a shovel. man!

270
00:18:06.035 --> 00:18:07.919
I didn't know what else to do!

271
00:18:07.987 --> 00:18:10.505
So I just... I tied him up
and I put him in the backroom

272
00:18:10.573 --> 00:18:11.789
with that other country hick.

273
00:18:11.858 --> 00:18:13.491
Here we go. Here we go.

274
00:18:13.543 --> 00:18:15.442
I came through. you gimp!

275
00:18:15.512 --> 00:18:17.027
Who was he calling?

276
00:18:17.096 --> 00:18:18.796
The Sheriff.

277
00:18:18.865 --> 00:18:21.115
Man. I don't know. dude.

278
00:18:21.183 --> 00:18:22.261
It just... It set off...

279
00:18:22.285 --> 00:18:23.751
Did the call go through?

280
00:18:23.820 --> 00:18:25.347
Maybe. man. What
do you mean maybe?

281
00:18:25.371 --> 00:18:26.514
Did the call go through?

282
00:18:26.538 --> 00:18:28.723
Yes. No. I don't know!

283
00:18:28.791 --> 00:18:30.574
I don't know. man.

284
00:18:33.129 --> 00:18:34.762
Yo. but I got the gear.

285
00:18:35.564 --> 00:18:36.804
We got to move on this now.

286
00:18:36.833 --> 00:18:38.215
(DOORBELL RINGS)

287
00:18:38.785 --> 00:18:39.934
Yes?

288
00:18:41.187 --> 00:18:43.887
Sorry to bother you.
ma'am. Is your electricity out?

289
00:18:45.090 --> 00:18:47.341
Excuse me. I'm looking
for a Harold Jenkins.

290
00:18:47.410 --> 00:18:48.892
JENKINS: Right here.

291
00:18:50.529 --> 00:18:52.246
Alexander Mahone. FBI.

292
00:18:52.314 --> 00:18:54.426
I'm staying 50 feet
away from her at all times.

293
00:18:54.450 --> 00:18:56.617
What the hell else
does she want?

294
00:18:56.702 --> 00:18:58.402
I'm not here about that.

295
00:18:59.388 --> 00:19:00.571
What are you here for?

296
00:19:00.623 --> 00:19:02.355
D.B. Cooper.

297
00:19:02.424 --> 00:19:04.291
People still want to
know about that guy?

298
00:19:04.360 --> 00:19:06.460
(LAUGHS) Unbelievable.

299
00:19:06.528 --> 00:19:09.568
You worked the gas station in
American Fork where he filled up.

300
00:19:09.598 --> 00:19:11.132
Yeah.

301
00:19:11.200 --> 00:19:14.134
Normal looking guy.
Barely said a word.

302
00:19:14.203 --> 00:19:18.022
There were some discrepancies in
the statement you filed 30 years ago.

303
00:19:18.090 --> 00:19:22.092
In the report. it's noted that
you said he filled up at 7:00 a.m.

304
00:19:22.161 --> 00:19:25.529
But on another occasion.
you said it was 7:00 p.m.

305
00:19:25.598 --> 00:19:26.781
Which was it?

306
00:19:26.849 --> 00:19:27.982
Both.

307
00:19:29.302 --> 00:19:30.801
He gassed up twice?

308
00:19:30.869 --> 00:19:32.036
Yeah.

309
00:19:33.039 --> 00:19:34.839
Full tanks both times?

310
00:19:35.608 --> 00:19:37.475
Yeah. Why?

311
00:19:39.011 --> 00:19:41.295
JEANETTE: A systems what?

312
00:19:41.363 --> 00:19:43.658
It's a systems diagnostics test.

313
00:19:43.682 --> 00:19:45.310
Footage from our
gopher cam picked up

314
00:19:45.334 --> 00:19:47.768
exactly where your
line was corrupted.

315
00:19:47.837 --> 00:19:49.470
And who corrupted it?

316
00:19:50.005 --> 00:19:51.255
You guys?

317
00:19:51.324 --> 00:19:52.473
Maybe.

318
00:19:52.541 --> 00:19:54.086
All I know is my
supervisor called

319
00:19:54.110 --> 00:19:55.721
and said he wants me and my crew

320
00:19:55.745 --> 00:19:58.962
to get over here and fix that
problem double quick. double time.

321
00:20:00.249 --> 00:20:04.819
So. you're not with
the electric company?

322
00:20:04.887 --> 00:20:08.372
No. ma'am. Now feel
free to call your company.

323
00:20:08.441 --> 00:20:10.686
But I should tell you. all they'll
do is send over some tech.

324
00:20:10.710 --> 00:20:12.776
maybe tomorrow if you're lucky.

325
00:20:12.845 --> 00:20:15.579
And he'll spend a whole
day trying to find the problem

326
00:20:15.648 --> 00:20:18.716
and another
day trying to fix it.

327
00:20:18.785 --> 00:20:21.084
But we're here right now

328
00:20:21.153 --> 00:20:23.788
and we're ready to
turn your juice back on.

329
00:20:25.107 --> 00:20:26.507
My juice?

330
00:20:26.575 --> 00:20:27.958
That's right.

331
00:20:30.329 --> 00:20:31.728
And...

332
00:20:33.015 --> 00:20:36.383
And that's your crew?

333
00:20:40.205 --> 00:20:41.839
Yes. ma'am.

334
00:20:41.907 --> 00:20:46.093
Yeah. D.B. Cooper was
driving a 1965 Chevy Nova.

335
00:20:46.161 --> 00:20:48.579
There's no record on file
that Cooper even had a car.

336
00:20:48.648 --> 00:20:51.477
But Charles Westmoreland did. and
the car registered to him at the time

337
00:20:51.501 --> 00:20:55.069
was a 1965 Chevy Nova
with a 16-gallon gas tank.

338
00:20:55.137 --> 00:20:59.340
Back then. a Chevy that size got
approximately eight miles to the gallon?

339
00:20:59.408 --> 00:21:02.037
Now. D.B. stopped at the
station in American Fork

340
00:21:02.061 --> 00:21:03.822
and gassed up
once early that day.

341
00:21:03.846 --> 00:21:06.558
and then came back later that
same night and gassed up again.

342
00:21:06.582 --> 00:21:08.516
<i>Now. why would a
guy headed to Mexico.</i>

343
00:21:08.584 --> 00:21:10.451
<i>which is a straight shot south.</i>

344
00:21:10.520 --> 00:21:12.853
<i>drive off the main road
for an all-day detour?</i>

345
00:21:12.922 --> 00:21:14.822
The money. Exactly.

346
00:21:14.890 --> 00:21:19.877
Cooper. Westmoreland jumped
out of a plane with $5 million.

347
00:21:19.946 --> 00:21:22.880
But Westmoreland didn't have the
money on him when he was arrested.

348
00:21:22.949 --> 00:21:24.481
He ditched it before
he got caught.

349
00:21:24.550 --> 00:21:26.033
Give me that magic marker.

350
00:21:26.101 --> 00:21:27.818
From American Fork.
he couldn't have gone

351
00:21:27.887 --> 00:21:30.170
further than 64
miles in any direction.

352
00:21:30.239 --> 00:21:32.290
I want everything you've
got in that perimeter.

353
00:21:32.358 --> 00:21:33.835
Those cons are in
one of these towns.

354
00:21:33.859 --> 00:21:36.155
and if there's so much as a
cat missing in one of them.

355
00:21:36.179 --> 00:21:37.678
I want to know about it.

356
00:21:41.284 --> 00:21:44.968
The defective cable runs
right beneath your garage.

357
00:21:45.037 --> 00:21:47.872
We're gonna have to
dig up the floor to get to it.

358
00:21:49.408 --> 00:21:50.836
Well. who's gonna pay for this

359
00:21:50.860 --> 00:21:53.493
and what about the
cleanup and the repair?

360
00:21:53.562 --> 00:21:56.696
Well. the company
will cover all costs.

361
00:21:56.765 --> 00:21:58.298
We'll just dig a small trench.

362
00:21:58.367 --> 00:22:00.434
once we're finished.
we'll re-lay the cement.

363
00:22:00.502 --> 00:22:02.269
It'll look as good as new.

364
00:22:02.355 --> 00:22:04.588
JEANETTE: How
long is it going to take?

365
00:22:04.656 --> 00:22:07.774
One way or another.
we'll be out of here today.

366
00:22:07.860 --> 00:22:11.562
We really need to
get started. ma'am.

367
00:22:11.631 --> 00:22:14.376
Wouldn't want a pretty
little thing like yourself

368
00:22:14.400 --> 00:22:17.067
sitting in the dark
tonight. now. would we?

369
00:22:17.136 --> 00:22:20.370
Well. that depends
on who I'm sitting with.

370
00:22:21.407 --> 00:22:22.590
Touche.

371
00:22:26.579 --> 00:22:28.312
Fine.

372
00:22:28.381 --> 00:22:31.415
It's okay. y'all go ahead and
do whatever y'all need to do.

373
00:22:31.484 --> 00:22:34.084
Jeanette. the noise
might be substantial.

374
00:22:34.153 --> 00:22:36.753
You might wanna take in
that tennis game after all.

375
00:22:36.822 --> 00:22:40.023
Oh. no. it's too
hot for that now.

376
00:22:40.092 --> 00:22:42.426
Plus. I'm gonna
keep an eye on y'all

377
00:22:42.495 --> 00:22:44.762
and make sure you
don't steal anything.

378
00:22:44.830 --> 00:22:46.046
Ma'am.

379
00:22:47.566 --> 00:22:48.566
Oh.

380
00:22:50.969 --> 00:22:52.870
How are you? Good.

381
00:22:55.591 --> 00:22:56.957
All right. where's Tweener?

382
00:22:57.026 --> 00:22:59.143
He's next door plugging
the extension cord.

383
00:22:59.211 --> 00:23:01.495
We're going to have
to cut up the cement.

384
00:23:01.563 --> 00:23:04.231
Yo. we gots company.

385
00:23:09.805 --> 00:23:11.371
What's up. Snowflake?

386
00:23:17.063 --> 00:23:19.730
Well. as always.
your timing is flawless.

387
00:23:21.083 --> 00:23:22.216
I don't follow.

388
00:23:22.285 --> 00:23:23.900
Well. let me try
and explain it to you.

389
00:23:23.969 --> 00:23:25.603
We're trying to
run something here

390
00:23:25.671 --> 00:23:27.821
and we can't have people
walking in off the street.

391
00:23:27.890 --> 00:23:29.339
Oh.

392
00:23:29.408 --> 00:23:31.341
Oh. okay. so you
want us to leave

393
00:23:31.410 --> 00:23:33.443
and then you can
just mail us the check.

394
00:23:35.748 --> 00:23:38.232
Sucre. I know you trust me.

395
00:23:38.301 --> 00:23:40.412
And you know I'll cut
you in on that money.

396
00:23:40.436 --> 00:23:44.054
But the two of you being here
right now jeopardizes everything.

397
00:23:45.474 --> 00:23:47.607
I'm not going nowhere.

398
00:23:47.676 --> 00:23:49.309
I want my share of the money.

399
00:23:49.378 --> 00:23:50.739
C-NOTE: Wait a
minute. Hold on. man.

400
00:23:50.763 --> 00:23:52.946
Ain't we did this dance before?

401
00:23:53.015 --> 00:23:56.166
You know. I say I
want in. you say no.

402
00:23:56.235 --> 00:24:00.437
Then I threaten to tell somebody
about what's going on here.

403
00:24:00.506 --> 00:24:01.872
And then you decide to play nice

404
00:24:01.940 --> 00:24:03.857
and then we're one
big happy family.

405
00:24:05.511 --> 00:24:08.212
Why don't we just stop
wasting time. all right?

406
00:24:13.552 --> 00:24:14.902
Thank you.

407
00:24:22.477 --> 00:24:24.545
Damn. man. you still alive?

408
00:24:26.849 --> 00:24:28.799
And kicking. homeboy.

409
00:24:28.868 --> 00:24:30.517
How did you find us?

410
00:24:30.586 --> 00:24:33.837
Man. if I can do a rapid deployment
of satellite communications

411
00:24:33.905 --> 00:24:35.622
for Uncle Sam all
over the world...

412
00:24:35.691 --> 00:24:36.840
(KNOCKING AT DOOR)

413
00:24:36.909 --> 00:24:38.992
How are you guys doing?

414
00:24:40.346 --> 00:24:43.063
Who are you? Who are they?

415
00:24:43.132 --> 00:24:45.716
I had to call my supervisor.

416
00:24:45.785 --> 00:24:48.501
He sent them right over.
This job is a top priority.

417
00:24:48.570 --> 00:24:52.206
We want to get this done as
quickly and efficiently as possible.

418
00:25:04.453 --> 00:25:06.019
Well. Jeanette. like I said.

419
00:25:06.088 --> 00:25:08.905
there's a lot of work to do
and it's going to be noisy.

420
00:25:08.974 --> 00:25:11.141
Oh. drinks. I forgot to ask.

421
00:25:12.027 --> 00:25:13.660
We're good. Thanks.

422
00:25:23.789 --> 00:25:25.889
Yo. man. this is not good.

423
00:25:25.957 --> 00:25:29.643
We got her up in our grill
checking in on us all the time.

424
00:25:29.711 --> 00:25:32.045
The boy is right.

425
00:25:32.114 --> 00:25:37.051
And since I can't dig. I'll
volunteer to keep her occupied.

426
00:25:38.237 --> 00:25:39.870
You don't touch her.

427
00:25:39.938 --> 00:25:41.916
Who are you.
Sister Mary Francis?

428
00:25:41.940 --> 00:25:43.791
I know how to play nice.

429
00:25:44.526 --> 00:25:46.076
I'll be watching.

430
00:26:18.711 --> 00:26:20.577
<i>(SOFT JAZZ MUSIC PLAYING)</i>

431
00:26:38.631 --> 00:26:41.064
Billy? Is that you?

432
00:26:49.691 --> 00:26:51.825
Billy? Is that you?

433
00:26:56.531 --> 00:26:57.597
Yup.

434
00:27:04.590 --> 00:27:06.356
Thank you kindly. Mmm-hmm.

435
00:27:08.861 --> 00:27:12.428
Well. now. how did
you get out of working?

436
00:27:14.015 --> 00:27:16.116
Union rules.

437
00:27:16.201 --> 00:27:19.536
One crew member always
has to supervise. Ah.

438
00:27:19.604 --> 00:27:22.005
I'll check on them in a bit.

439
00:27:25.243 --> 00:27:27.323
Lemonade? Mmm.

440
00:27:29.514 --> 00:27:30.514
Hmm.

441
00:27:34.603 --> 00:27:36.036
A little more ice.

442
00:27:40.175 --> 00:27:41.308
Yeah.

443
00:27:42.361 --> 00:27:44.528
There we go.

444
00:27:44.597 --> 00:27:48.148
And I like mine
with a little oomph.

445
00:27:48.216 --> 00:27:54.955
But since you're on the clock.
I guess you can't join me?

446
00:27:57.860 --> 00:27:59.343
Just two fingers.

447
00:28:05.217 --> 00:28:07.051
(BOTH LAUGHING)

448
00:28:23.486 --> 00:28:25.002
Been a while.

449
00:28:25.070 --> 00:28:26.219
Yeah?

450
00:28:32.161 --> 00:28:36.196
Whiskey always
makes me feel irascible.

451
00:28:37.900 --> 00:28:39.800
I don't know what that means.

452
00:28:41.236 --> 00:28:44.070
But I do like the sound of it.

453
00:28:49.928 --> 00:28:52.395
Are you wearing Angel perfume?

454
00:28:54.283 --> 00:28:55.582
I am.

455
00:28:59.755 --> 00:29:02.222
Oh. Hmm.

456
00:29:03.559 --> 00:29:06.159
That reminds you
of an ex. I take it.

457
00:29:07.363 --> 00:29:08.562
Yeah.

458
00:29:10.399 --> 00:29:16.536
Now. was that good
memories or bad memories?

459
00:29:19.140 --> 00:29:20.240
Both.

460
00:29:30.552 --> 00:29:32.085
Did you talk to Maricruz?

461
00:29:32.154 --> 00:29:34.194
I don't want to talk about it.

462
00:29:35.540 --> 00:29:37.941
I got to get some
water or something.

463
00:29:38.009 --> 00:29:40.710
Use the hose on the
other side of the house.

464
00:29:43.415 --> 00:29:48.134
Sucre. down the road.
if you're in trouble.

465
00:29:48.203 --> 00:29:50.637
Europeangoldfinch.net.

466
00:29:53.225 --> 00:29:55.508
It's what we can all
use to communicate.

467
00:29:55.577 --> 00:29:57.660
Post a note on
the message board.

468
00:29:59.681 --> 00:30:00.880
What's it called?

469
00:30:00.949 --> 00:30:02.633
Europeangoldfinch.net.

470
00:30:03.835 --> 00:30:05.569
That's a bird. right?

471
00:30:12.228 --> 00:30:13.677
I got something.

472
00:30:20.686 --> 00:30:22.197
SCOFIELD: It's
the silo's foundation.

473
00:30:22.221 --> 00:30:23.620
Hells. yeah.

474
00:30:24.390 --> 00:30:26.356
Thank you. Charles.

475
00:30:26.424 --> 00:30:31.361
We just need to find the
edge and dig underneath it.

476
00:30:31.429 --> 00:30:35.031
We'll get the money.
hit the back roads.

477
00:30:35.517 --> 00:30:36.983
Uh...

478
00:30:37.052 --> 00:30:39.012
Well... What's wrong?

479
00:30:41.423 --> 00:30:45.458
We gots to stop in Tooele
first and gas up the ride.

480
00:30:45.527 --> 00:30:46.837
I thought you already did that.

481
00:30:46.861 --> 00:30:48.845
Man. when the garden
center thing happened.

482
00:30:48.914 --> 00:30:50.847
I just forgot. all right?

483
00:30:52.350 --> 00:30:54.417
I want you to go back into town.

484
00:30:54.486 --> 00:30:56.564
I want you to gas up that car.

485
00:30:56.588 --> 00:30:58.454
Because I'm not driving around

486
00:30:58.524 --> 00:31:00.485
with millions of dollars in
the trunk. Do you understand?

487
00:31:00.509 --> 00:31:02.959
Man. why do I gots to do it?

488
00:31:03.028 --> 00:31:04.210
Okay.

489
00:31:05.497 --> 00:31:06.697
Okay.

490
00:31:16.591 --> 00:31:18.725
SCOFIELD: I better
check in on our friend.

491
00:31:19.694 --> 00:31:21.027
(T-BAG LAUGHING)

492
00:31:22.414 --> 00:31:26.116
You got it on time.
Miss Tinsel Toes.

493
00:31:26.185 --> 00:31:27.425
(T-BAG CHUCKLES)

494
00:31:35.844 --> 00:31:37.010
Billy?

495
00:31:39.814 --> 00:31:40.980
Billy?

496
00:31:42.217 --> 00:31:43.650
Yeah.

497
00:31:43.718 --> 00:31:46.019
I made you a sandwich.

498
00:31:46.104 --> 00:31:49.072
Peanut butter and jelly
with the crusts cut off.

499
00:31:49.942 --> 00:31:51.541
Just like you like.

500
00:31:56.381 --> 00:31:58.448
I'm so glad you came back.

501
00:31:59.968 --> 00:32:02.301
I don't want to
say I told you so.

502
00:32:02.371 --> 00:32:04.637
but that was just
not the girl for you.

503
00:32:11.129 --> 00:32:12.629
Where is that?

504
00:32:13.615 --> 00:32:15.415
Where's what. sweetheart?

505
00:32:16.251 --> 00:32:17.750
That painting.

506
00:32:18.954 --> 00:32:20.720
It's Holland.

507
00:32:20.789 --> 00:32:23.122
Where I grew up. You know that.

508
00:32:24.926 --> 00:32:26.459
It's beautiful.

509
00:32:26.528 --> 00:32:28.794
Oh. there's no place better.

510
00:32:28.863 --> 00:32:31.315
It's so peaceful. so...

511
00:32:31.383 --> 00:32:34.684
So protected from
this crazy world.

512
00:32:49.601 --> 00:32:52.035
<i>MAN: Operator.</i>
(WHISPERING) Hello. operator.

513
00:32:52.103 --> 00:32:53.903
There's an intruder in my house.

514
00:32:59.228 --> 00:33:01.712
<i>Hello. ma'am?
Ma'am. are you there?</i>

515
00:33:03.014 --> 00:33:04.648
<i>Is anyone there?</i>

516
00:33:08.620 --> 00:33:11.298
MAHONE: Heard you had
some activity in Tooele today.

517
00:33:11.322 --> 00:33:14.107
A bit. Don't see how it
warrants a visit from the FBI.

518
00:33:14.175 --> 00:33:16.221
A stolen car was dumped
just outside of town

519
00:33:16.245 --> 00:33:18.006
belonging to a woman who
went to school in St. Louis.

520
00:33:18.030 --> 00:33:19.270
Am I getting that right?

521
00:33:19.314 --> 00:33:21.081
Yes. sir.

522
00:33:21.150 --> 00:33:23.861
And then here. the owner's
girlfriend reports him missing.

523
00:33:23.885 --> 00:33:25.680
and then his buddy
comes by to check it out

524
00:33:25.704 --> 00:33:28.271
and he goes missing. too.

525
00:33:28.323 --> 00:33:30.451
Yeah. but Woody and Chet have
been known to drop everything

526
00:33:30.475 --> 00:33:33.426
and go boar hunting when
the opportunity presents itself.

527
00:33:33.495 --> 00:33:35.778
and they don't
tell their old ladies.

528
00:33:39.651 --> 00:33:41.684
Mr. Mahone. I'll bet
you my lunch money

529
00:33:41.753 --> 00:33:43.873
there's nothing
amiss around here.

530
00:33:45.707 --> 00:33:47.852
His dad will be showing
up soon with the keys

531
00:33:47.876 --> 00:33:49.838
and you can look for yourself.

532
00:33:49.862 --> 00:33:52.279
Whoa! What are you doing?

533
00:33:58.587 --> 00:34:00.253
Mr. Mahone.

534
00:34:00.322 --> 00:34:01.687
(SHUSHING)

535
00:34:01.756 --> 00:34:03.289
(MUFFLED YELLS)

536
00:34:14.702 --> 00:34:15.835
They're here.

537
00:34:15.904 --> 00:34:18.304
Those escaped convicts.
they're here in town.

538
00:34:49.771 --> 00:34:51.071
Who's there?

539
00:34:51.990 --> 00:34:53.990
It's the police. ma'am.

540
00:34:54.058 --> 00:34:55.058
You okay?

541
00:34:55.109 --> 00:34:56.325
Yes.

542
00:34:58.780 --> 00:35:00.241
Can you tell me what happened?

543
00:35:00.265 --> 00:35:02.933
There was this strange man.

544
00:35:03.001 --> 00:35:06.636
I made him a peanut
butter and jelly sandwich.

545
00:35:06.705 --> 00:35:08.321
I thought he was Billy.

546
00:35:12.928 --> 00:35:16.129
And once the kids went
to sleep. we'd take a bath.

547
00:35:18.299 --> 00:35:21.184
A long bath.

548
00:35:21.236 --> 00:35:25.672
And afterwards. I'd just
sit there and watch her

549
00:35:25.740 --> 00:35:28.140
do her routine. see?

550
00:35:28.210 --> 00:35:31.077
Rub her lotion
on. comb her hair.

551
00:35:31.163 --> 00:35:34.764
Dress up in her
nighttime fineries.

552
00:35:34.833 --> 00:35:36.833
Oh. you're killing me.

553
00:35:37.769 --> 00:35:39.435
(INHALING DEEPLY)

554
00:35:39.504 --> 00:35:43.623
She had this spot
on her neck right here.

555
00:35:46.244 --> 00:35:48.144
Gave her goose bumps every time.

556
00:35:53.869 --> 00:35:55.936
And that perfume...

557
00:36:01.977 --> 00:36:03.409
My ex.

558
00:36:04.596 --> 00:36:06.429
he was an accountant.

559
00:36:07.533 --> 00:36:10.266
He was really buttoned up.

560
00:36:10.335 --> 00:36:14.287
It was. "Wham. bam.
thank you. Sam."

561
00:36:15.907 --> 00:36:17.541
Oh. shame on him.

562
00:36:20.679 --> 00:36:25.248
Why did it end with that
lady you were talking about?

563
00:36:31.673 --> 00:36:33.540
Just went our separate ways.

564
00:36:40.865 --> 00:36:45.535
Do you know what I think the
best cure is for a broken heart?

565
00:36:47.805 --> 00:36:49.072
Do tell.

566
00:36:50.776 --> 00:36:52.576
Get back on the bike.

567
00:36:54.512 --> 00:36:56.112
Whatever bike it is.

568
00:36:57.749 --> 00:36:59.049
(CHUCKLING)

569
00:37:00.452 --> 00:37:02.218
Amen to that.

570
00:37:03.722 --> 00:37:05.288
Speaking of...

571
00:37:07.659 --> 00:37:09.876
Could you do something for me?

572
00:37:12.163 --> 00:37:13.829
I'm certain of it.

573
00:37:16.851 --> 00:37:18.184
Come here.

574
00:37:20.522 --> 00:37:23.106
Only you have to
be very discreet.

575
00:37:25.227 --> 00:37:27.527
They don't come any discreeter.

576
00:37:28.296 --> 00:37:31.614
You know that big guy.

577
00:37:31.683 --> 00:37:36.936
the strong guy that
doesn't speak much?

578
00:37:37.005 --> 00:37:39.439
Would you go in
there and ask him

579
00:37:39.507 --> 00:37:44.677
if he would like to have a drink
with me after he punches out?

580
00:37:44.746 --> 00:37:45.878
Please.

581
00:37:48.099 --> 00:37:51.050
You've just been playing me
this whole time. haven't you?

582
00:37:51.118 --> 00:37:52.358
Come on.

583
00:37:53.187 --> 00:37:55.889
Don't be like that.

584
00:37:55.957 --> 00:37:59.325
Would you just go out and
ask your friend? Please?

585
00:38:16.861 --> 00:38:18.828
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

586
00:38:21.566 --> 00:38:23.845
Hey. Dad. Sara. I've
been trying to reach you.

587
00:38:23.869 --> 00:38:27.287
Yeah. I've been meeting with
my defense attorneys all day.

588
00:38:27.355 --> 00:38:28.520
You in Washington?

589
00:38:28.589 --> 00:38:31.424
Yeah. but I'm coming
back on the next flight.

590
00:38:31.492 --> 00:38:33.120
I thought you were going
to be there for a while.

591
00:38:33.144 --> 00:38:34.877
No. no. Plan's changed. okay.

592
00:38:34.929 --> 00:38:36.362
<i>Sara. do you remember that guy</i>

593
00:38:36.431 --> 00:38:38.748
<i>that I met with you
in your apartment?</i>

594
00:38:38.817 --> 00:38:40.600
I want you to stay
away from him.

595
00:38:40.685 --> 00:38:42.886
Who. Lance? From my group?

596
00:38:42.954 --> 00:38:45.855
Yeah. yeah. that's him.
He is not who he says he is.

597
00:38:45.907 --> 00:38:48.140
<i>I found out some
other things. too.</i>

598
00:38:48.209 --> 00:38:50.393
What are you talking
about? <i>You were right.</i>

599
00:38:51.779 --> 00:38:53.746
<i>Sara?</i> I gotta go.

600
00:38:58.453 --> 00:38:59.835
<i>(COUNTRY MUSIC PLAYING)</i>

601
00:39:03.758 --> 00:39:05.541
CLERK: Yeah. that's right.

602
00:39:11.516 --> 00:39:12.916
Yo.

603
00:39:12.968 --> 00:39:14.300
Just one second. sir.

604
00:39:15.554 --> 00:39:16.794
Thank you.

605
00:39:17.906 --> 00:39:18.949
Can I help you?

606
00:39:18.973 --> 00:39:20.840
Just put 40 on three.

607
00:39:20.909 --> 00:39:23.676
I'm sorry. What pump was that?

608
00:39:23.745 --> 00:39:25.995
Three. Oh. that
one's been sticking.

609
00:39:26.063 --> 00:39:27.625
Okay. well. then.
I'll move the car.

610
00:39:27.649 --> 00:39:29.064
No. Don't trouble yourself.

611
00:39:29.133 --> 00:39:31.995
I'll have the mechanic
come out and pump it for you.

612
00:39:32.019 --> 00:39:33.664
Hey. we got a customer
waiting on three!

613
00:39:33.688 --> 00:39:35.149
MECHANIC: All
right. I'll be right there.

614
00:39:35.173 --> 00:39:37.106
Yo. look. man. I'm
in a hurry. all right?

615
00:39:37.158 --> 00:39:39.792
Oh. he'll be right
out. Just one second.

616
00:39:50.354 --> 00:39:51.470
(SIREN WAILING)

617
00:40:28.810 --> 00:40:29.825
(DOG BARKING)

618
00:40:41.656 --> 00:40:42.822
(GUN FIRES)

619
00:40:44.976 --> 00:40:48.627
Put your hands behind your
head and drop to your knees.

620
00:40:48.696 --> 00:40:50.429
Oh. God. Drop!

621
00:40:53.685 --> 00:40:55.217
Where are they?

622
00:40:57.305 --> 00:40:58.871
(PANTING)

623
00:41:01.376 --> 00:41:04.794
Where are they?

624
00:41:07.282 --> 00:41:08.380
Hey. man.

625
00:41:08.449 --> 00:41:09.843
One hand or
not. I think hillbilly

626
00:41:09.867 --> 00:41:11.211
needs to be up in here digging.

627
00:41:11.235 --> 00:41:12.518
What you think?

628
00:41:21.362 --> 00:41:22.628
Good man.

629
00:41:43.201 --> 00:41:45.112
What the hell are
you doing up here?

630
00:41:45.136 --> 00:41:46.619
Oh. I'm sorry. Jeanette.

631
00:41:46.687 --> 00:41:47.921
(TOILET FLUSHING)

632
00:41:47.989 --> 00:41:49.722
I just didn't see
you downstairs.

633
00:41:49.791 --> 00:41:51.568
I heard something. I
apologize for barging in.

634
00:41:51.592 --> 00:41:53.192
Don't bother.

635
00:41:53.261 --> 00:41:55.728
She's got the hots
for the big. strong one.

636
00:41:55.797 --> 00:41:58.175
I'm sorry. Jeanette. We're
gonna get back to work now.

637
00:41:58.199 --> 00:42:02.652
No. I think y'all are done. and
I think y'all need to leave now.

638
00:42:03.371 --> 00:42:04.581
We're almost finished.

639
00:42:04.605 --> 00:42:06.689
No. I think you
are finished. okay?

640
00:42:06.757 --> 00:42:08.917
And I want you to
leave my house now.

641
00:42:10.278 --> 00:42:11.511
(CAR APPROACHING)

642
00:42:15.416 --> 00:42:17.099
Sucre. check it out.

643
00:42:22.791 --> 00:42:24.871
<i>(DISPATCHER CHATTERING
ON POLICE RADIO)</i>

644
00:42:29.397 --> 00:42:30.546
Cop.

645
00:42:34.252 --> 00:42:35.784
JEANETTE: Oh. thank God.

646
00:42:42.743 --> 00:42:43.893
T-BAG: Where are you going?

647
00:42:43.962 --> 00:42:44.910
SCOFIELD: T-Bag. let her go.

648
00:42:44.979 --> 00:42:46.763
Oh. God.

649
00:42:46.815 --> 00:42:49.432
T-BAG: She's our only
way out of this. pretty.

650
00:42:51.869 --> 00:42:53.981
Don't say a word. you old whore.

651
00:42:54.005 --> 00:42:56.165
or I'm gonna cut
your throat out.

651
00:42:57.305 --> 00:43:57.768
-== [ www.OpenSubtitles.org ] ==-
